very aggressive: at 3.5 each U, and 8 days of symptomatic transmission,
the first LTC infection was carried by #27 as BLUE in generation 345
by gen 495 which is 150 generations or 6 days and 6 hrs later, we have one susceptible left, 11 symptomatc, 23 pre-symptomatic, and 15 incubating!
In the rest of the environment,
HOME has 23 susceptibles, and at present, there are 13 persons symptomatic at home, and 11 pre-symptomatic with 3 incubating
The ChildCare situation is
at 3pm pn Day 20, everyone there had been infected, there are 7 symptomatic and 4 inerts (past symptomatic phase)….
Have to look at console.log to see how many childcare attendees are so far spared, if any
We will now try 3.5 each U with 3 days of symptomatic transmission
Note that 3.5 is probably too high even for the childcare and family alone
The fact that it worked out in the trial last night does not state that is was the average setting, just that this setting produced desired results
Let's try with 3.5 nd 3 days red
so we get 18 infected with 15 identified cases as symptomatic, 9 infected in U8 (home)
we want to tone down U8 just a bit to say 3.3 later run
for now, at this point
U1 has no one (#27 not infected yet)
Not happening
